GEMINI-TERMINAL(1)                User Commands                GEMINI-TERMINAL(1)

NAME
    gemini-terminal - Bash-only dependency-light Gemini terminal chat client

SYNOPSIS
    gemini-terminal [session_name]
    gemini-terminal --resume <session_name>
    gemini-terminal --list
    gemini-terminal --models
    gemini-terminal --update-models
    gemini-terminal --select-model [--save]
    gemini-terminal --test-model <model_id> [--save]
    gemini-terminal --set-api-key
    gemini-terminal --attach FILE [session_name]
    gemini-terminal --credits
    gemini-terminal --doctor
    gemini-terminal --version
    gemini-terminal --help

DESCRIPTION
    gemini-terminal is the Bash-only implementation of gemini-terminal-tools.
    It is designed for systems where Python 3 is unavailable or undesirable,
    while still preserving the project's mission: a robust end-user terminal
    chat client rather than a curl example.

    It uses Bash, curl, and common Unix text tools.  jq is optional when
    available.  Without Python or jq, JSON handling is best-effort, so the
    Python-assisted Bash and ncurses versions remain more reliable.

USAGE
    Start a chat:

        gemini-terminal

    Start or reopen a named chat:

        gemini-terminal android-backup

    List sessions:

        gemini-terminal --list

    Update model cache:

        gemini-terminal --update-models

    Select a model:

        gemini-terminal --select-model

    Test a model:

        gemini-terminal --test-model gemini-2.5-flash

INPUT
    Type or paste a message, then press Ctrl+D to send.  Ctrl+C exits.

CONFIGURATION
    Shared config file:

        ~/.config/gemini-cli/config

    Supported keys include MODEL, CONTEXT_TURNS, GEMINI_API_KEY, SESSION_DIR,
    ATTACHMENT_DIR, MODEL_TEST_PROMPT, STARTUP_NOTICE, and model filter keys.

DEPENDENCIES
    Required:
        bash, curl, sed, awk, grep, tr, base64, mktemp, printf

    Optional:
        jq, file

LIMITATIONS
    - JSON handling is best-effort without jq.
    - Media attachment support is best-effort and depends on model/API support.
    - This edition intentionally avoids Python.

VERSION
    gemini-terminal version 0.3.0-bash-only

AUTHOR
    Part of the gemini-terminal-tools project.
